PrecisEnactment of the AGRICULTURAL MARKETING PROGRAMS REGULATIONS which define or explain the circumstances whereby a producer ceases to own or be responsible for marketing a crop, the formula for establishing the liability of both the administrator and the Government, how advances are to be attributed to an individual producer, the limits on how much of any particular crop may be sold by a producer without proof to that effect, and the conditions that must be complied with before payment of a guarantee.
RegistrationRegistration: SOR/ 1999-0295 Publication Date: 1999-07-07
Attachments
precis:
Enactment of the AGRICULTURAL MARKETING PROGRAMS REGULATIONS which define
or explain the circumstances whereby a producer ceases to own or be
responsible for marketing a crop, the formula for establishing the
liability of both the administrator and the Government, how advances are
to be attributed to an individual producer, the limits on how much of any
particular crop may be sold by a producer without proof to that effect, and
the conditions that must be complied with before payment of a guarantee.
